    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Text preprocessing transforms raw strings into a cleaner form suitable for analysis or model input. Classical NLP pipelines relied heavily on manual cleaning — lowercasing, stemming, stopword removal. Modern LLM agents delegate most token-level normalization to the model's tokenizer, but "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "strategic preprocessing",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " still affects retrieval quality, eval consistency, logging, and guardrail matching."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Text preprocessing covers operations applied before or alongside tokenization: Unicode normalization, whitespace cleanup, HTML or markdown stripping, language detection, sentence splitting, PII redaction, and deduplication. The goal is consistent, safe, searchable text without destroying meaning the downstream model needs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agents ingest messy real-world text — HTML emails, PDF extracts, chat logs with emoji and URLs. Poor preprocessing causes RAG retrieval misses (same word, different Unicode form), inflated token counts (unnecessary markup), privacy leaks (PII in logs), and inconsistent eval results. Preprocessing is the hygiene layer before embeddings, indexing, and LLM calls."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Consistent matching",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — normalization reduces duplicate variants in indexes"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Token efficiency",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — removing boilerplate saves context window space"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Safety and compliance",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — PII redaction before logging or third-party APIs"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Reliable evaluation",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — same preprocessing in train and inference pipelines"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Aggressive lowercasing or stemming can destroy case-sensitive identifiers (API keys, code)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Over-stripping punctuation hurts code, URLs, and structured formats"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Language-specific rules fail on multilingual agent traffic"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Preprocessing adds latency and must be replicated across services"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A typical agent ingestion pipeline applies steps in order: decode bytes to Unicode, normalize forms, strip unwanted markup, optionally redact sensitive patterns, then pass clean text to chunking and embedding."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import unicodedata\nimport re\nfrom bs4 import BeautifulSoup\n\ndef preprocess_for_rag(raw: str) -> str:\n    # Unicode normalization (NFKC collapses compatibility variants)\n    text = unicodedata.normalize(\"NFKC\", raw)\n    # Strip HTML if present\n    if \"<\" in text and \">\" in text:\n        text = BeautifulSoup(text, \"html.parser\").get_text(separator=\" \")\n    # Collapse excessive whitespace\n    text = re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \" \", text).strip()\n    return text\n\nsample = \"<p>café</p>  \\u00a0  Price: $9.99\"\nprint(preprocess_for_rag(sample))"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import re\n\nPII_PATTERNS = [\n    (re.compile(r\"\\b[\\w.-]+@[\\w.-]+\\.\\w+\\b\"), \"[EMAIL]\"),\n    (re.compile(r\"\\b\\d{3}-\\d{2}-\\d{4}\\b\"), \"[SSN]\"),\n]\n\ndef redact_pii(text: str) -> str:\n    for pattern, replacement in PII_PATTERNS:\n        text = pattern.sub(replacement, text)\n    return text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use it"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Always preprocess text before indexing for RAG. Preprocess eval datasets identically to production. Apply PII redaction before sending user content to external LLM APIs or storing in logs. Skip aggressive stemming or stopword removal before LLM tokenization — modern tokenizers handle raw text better than heavily normalized text."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Examples"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Two chunks \"café\" (composed é) and \"café\" (e + combining accent) fail to deduplicate without Unicode NFKC normalization. An agent indexing GitHub issues strips markdown image syntax to avoid polluting embeddings with repeated ![alt](url) tokens."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-world example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A document Q&A agent ingests Confluence HTML exports. Without preprocessing, average chunk size is 890 tokens; after HTML stripping, header normalization, and boilerplate removal, average chunk size drops to 520 tokens — fitting 40% more chunks in the same context window with improved retrieval precision."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Lowercasing code snippets before passing to coding agents"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Different preprocessing between indexing and query pipelines"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Removing all punctuation from structured data like JSON or SQL"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Assuming LLM tokenizers eliminate the need for document-level cleaning"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Apply Unicode NFKC normalization for indexing and search"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Preserve original text for display; store cleaned text for retrieval"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
